This feature includes the hardware to allow bottom exit, and other components for cable management and filler plates to preserve the recommended air circulation. Frame cable management A vertical cable management guide (“spine”) can assist with proper cable management for fiber, copper, and coupling cables (see Figure 11-3 on page 444). The spine is shipped with configurations that contain either three PCIe+ I/O drawers and/or two CPC drawers. All external cabling to the system (from top or bottom) can use the spine to minimize interference with the PDUs mounted on the sides of the frame.
